            <abstract>
                <p>In a town called Wandige, there was a church devoted to Mary, and this church had a millstone used to grind wheat for the Eucharist. One day, a dog licked the millstone. The people reported the incident to the mayor, and he had the old millstone replaced with a new one. The dog came again a few days later, and just before it could lick the new millstone, Mary killed it. She made it rigid like stone, and it remained standing upright in the place where it died. The people praised Mary.</p>
            </abstract>
